text:
I have always come to this store, specially summer time and have never had any issues. Sometimes I pay and sometimes my boyfriend does, we have been asked for ID as we are about to pay.
Today we come in, to get some Tequila and Margarita mix for Memorial Day weekend at the pool, my boyfriend is about to pay and the cashier lady says she needs to see both of our IDs.
We have never been asked for both, there is no sign at the door saying they required to see ID for all people - only sign at the door refers to pets coming in. I tried to check online if this is a law and it does not appear so. I was not carrying my wallet but first of all I was not purchasing alcohol just company and second I am 43 years old - I look slightly younger but never under 21. I tried looking for a copy image of my DL which is in my photo library in my phone and the cashier refuses to accept that either. Then she pretends like she is all worried trying to "find" a solution on how can she sell my boyfriend with out me having an ID.
Well, no thank you. If this is how you guys treat customers, you won't be getting my business then.
And just to clarify, I was not intoxicated, dressed suspiciously (I had just gotten out of work) and like I said I do not look close to 21- any thing that may have caused the cashier not to sell.
ABC Helena, you need to have better customer service.
